HEADWORD: Twopence
<hw>Two"pence</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small coin,
and money of account, in England, equivalent to two pennies, -- minted
to a fixed annual amount, for almsgiving by the sovereign on Maundy
Thursday.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twopenny</ent>⟦br⟧
